Lord Blackwood was the furthest thing from my mind when I wrote this. I had just deleted terrible a psychic spider and I was thinking 

Then I figured it should be a male spider of a species where the females don't eat them so that the Foundation would worry about it getting around and breeding more psychic spiders, and I found a cool, fairly intelligent breed that loved to eat other spiders, I thought I was all set.

aaaand then somewhere around that point it switched completely to a story about how incredibly mind fuckingly large we are in comparison to tiny milimeter sized jumping spiders. For me the subtext is all about how when he finally sees the doctor for who she is he flips his tiny spider wig like a sailor spotting Cthulu.

Blackwood is a slug who should not be a slug. The spider was a normal spider that saw the closest thing to a god that it could conceive.







